emotes.msg: AllowBalorRobe
What a pretty piece of shell! But I can't do anything with it. Sorry.
What a pretty, and large, piece of shell! I'm afraid I haven't the faintest idea what to do with it, though.
This is a beautiful pearl! You should match your wardrobe around it!
How disgusting!
There is, however, a sage somewhere in the southern mountain range that actually likes those things. How revolting...
This is a nice shiny bauble! I can't do anything with it though. Maybe one of the outlaws in Bandit Castle can help you.
This is a nice shiny bauble! I can't do anything with it though. Maybe one of the outlaws in Bandit Castle can help you.
This is a nice shiny bauble! I can't do anything with it though. Maybe one of the outlaws in Bandit Castle can help you.
I can take the hides of certain creatures and turn them into items of value.
Have you the skins of armoredillos, gromnies, or reedsharks?	I can use them in my craft.
Yo-Jin holds the robe up reverently and looks a bit nervous.
Good thing I left enough here to make alterations... I'll just be a moment.
Whew, here you go. It'll fit over other armor pieces now.
Here you go. People have been telling me about a strange new plant that's been found in some dungeons and around the landscape. Quite a colorful thing, or so they say.
Here's your armor! I overheard someone talking about the new plants again. They sound so lovely! I'll bet someone with the proper skills could crush them up and make a fine dye.
Enjoy the armor! May it keep the burn off your back. Oh my! The plants are just all I can think about... It's a pity that I can't use them in my craft due to all the harsh chemicals I use.
I never thought I could make such a sturdy hide into a fine shirt like this! I hope it's not to scratchy on your skin!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
Here you go!
I find greaves so aesthetically pleasing. Even if they do come from those brutish reedsharks. Perchance have you tried dyeing your other pieces of armor?
A friend gave me a dyeing pot, but I don't seem to be able to dye any of the leather armor I craft from creature hides.
Reedsharks have such rough, ugly skin. Crafting from their skin always punishes my delicate hands!
By the way, have you tried dyeing armor yet? Try as I might, I just can't seem to get the knack of it!
Ah, another masterpiece! Such a drab, gray color though. It's quite a shame that I have to apply so many chemicals to treat the leather, otherwise they could be infused with such color!
It pains my heart to make such dowdy-colored armor. A pity this cannot be dyed.
Have you tried dyeing any other armor yet? Be careful... if you do a poor job you might damage your armor, and that would certainly be dreadful!
Wow, this thing reminds me of those strange Hoary Mattekar hides. Only, not as hoary, or protective, for that matter. But there is more material here to work with...
This is rather exotic! It is sort of a claw shield.
A Mattekar claw?  I don't think I can make clothing out of this one.  Well, here, have this.

Yes, the Hoary Mattekars are now back. Given the strangeness of creature migrations that have occurred over this past year, I would not be surprised were the Hoary to be a more permanent fixture on Dereth.	Here is your robe.
Yes, there's enough material here for me to let this out a bit... Very well, I'll just be a moment.
There you go. It'll fit over other armor pieces now.
Oh my! Will you just look at this drab old thing! I'll spruce it up for you and make you the star you were meant to be!
What's this? Warmer than the Hoary that is for sure. Hmm... This seems to be a mattekar who has adapted to a warmer climate. Interesting.
The hide is a little tougher, though not meant for the cold. Against heat however, this should do quite nicely.
The little shreths are kind of cute, aren't they? It is a pity that people have found a way to use their skin. Now they will be hunted like most of the other poor creatures of Dereth.
Some of the larger shreths are just coming into their own. They are aggressive not out of hostility, but out of fear. Killing them is not the answer!
In killing the shreth of today, we may be dooming our tomorrow. Perhaps the shreths hold an answer to an unforeseen plague, or some equally monumental task. I urge you to reconsider hunting them!
This probably came from a baby ursuin somewhere... Loincloths are so last year.
Ursuin make wonderful garments! Their coats make lovely coats that are functional too! Of course I can make a mattekar coat look even better than an ursuin one...
This is a pretty small shank of hide.  But never fear, Yi Yo Jin has never failed at making something both fashionable, and affordable!
Wow! Ursuin hides are so soft in the spring and summer season! Maybe I'll take the extra strips from your coat and line my breeches with them...
This tooth would make a fine implement of destruction. Take it, and strike down my enemies!
Ursuins certainly have large heads. Personally, I like their coats better than these helms.
This has just the splash of color that you'll need to really shine like a star!
Remember, snakeskin is like make-up.  Too much and it makes you look like a tawdry matron!
This helmet is nice because it goes with anything that you wear. Sclavus are so useful when they die.
This is large enough to craft into a well fitting cuirass I think.
Well then. I think that this may be the first of a great many new robes to come my friend. Make sure to show your friends.
Not quite as sturdy as the tanned red hide that I worked with before, but it's still strong enough and large enough to craft into a nice robe. Wear it well.
Let's see. The hide is thick and leathery, and aside from the small bony protrusions it's in fine shape. I think a nice set of leggings.
There you go.
Another fine specimen. A little thicker than the last shreth hide I was given to work with. Let me have a moment and I'll... Yes, yes that's it!
Here you go.
Where did you get this? It's rather frightening, and rancid smelling. Well, let me see what I can do with it.
Here you go.
I've seen something like this recently. Came from a carenzi though, it mottled and smelled rank. Much like this. Where are you finding these creatures?
Well, I've done the best I can.
What is this!? I've never seen anything like this. It will make a fine robe I think. Give me a moment.
Yes, there it is done.
I've seen some interesting hides pass my way, but the hides that people have been bringing me most recently are the oddest.
A few more threads...and done!
Be careful out there.
Will miracles never cease?  The Hoary Mattekar has returned!	A beautiful and ferocious creature.	 And most people looking at it see nothing but a robe.	Such a shame.  Give me the hide.
Yo-Jin holds the hide up reverently and looks a bit scared.
Well, I have Kresovus' permission to craft this hide now, but I'm still not sure I want to. You must be pretty important for Kresovus to allow this.
Yo-Jin hesitates and then begins his work, deftly cutting Balor's hide in the pattern for a robe.

Here you are. I don't mind saying that this is some of my best work. Be careful with this, I'm not sure Kresovus would be so giving if you let it come to harm. Oh, and be tactful, don't wear this around Kresovus.
Yi Yo-Jin rubs the fur between his fingers and peers closely at it.
This is a rather unusual Mattekar hide. Hmm, the last time I saw fur like this was when I visited Linvak Tu...
No, No, No! I am not going to be responsible for making a robe out of this hide.
What are you doing, trying to get me killed?
